===Levels 1–40: Repairing Motherlode Mine struts===
Repairing struts in the [[Motherlode Mine]] offers slow experience, but it does not cost money. Due to the diminishing returns it is not advised to do this past level 40. The struts can be fixed using a [[hammer]]. Repairing them grants [[Smithing]] [[experience]] equal to 1.5 times the player's Smithing level. A hammer can be found in the crates surrounding the machine. For the fastest repairing speed, players should hop to another world where the strut needs to be repaired, as usually there is at least one strut that needs repairing.

Experience rates scale depending on the Smithing level. Players can gain 12,000 [[experience]] per hour at level 10, increasing up to 24,000 experience per hour at level 40. 

===Levels 15–99: Blast Furnace===
Smelting bars (other than gold or silver) at the [[Blast Furnace]] offers slow experience, but it usually provides decent profit. Having the [[ice gloves]] and [[coal bag]] is strongly recommended to significantly increase the number of bars created per hour. Players will also need weight-reducing clothing and stamina potions to always have run energy. Optimal bar patterns can be found on the [[Blast Furnace#Bar Patterns]] page.

These numbers assume you are using one of the official worlds, are using a coal bag, are wearing ice gloves, and are using 36 stamina potion doses per hour.
{{:Blast Furnace/MMG table}}

